fields.name: Youth Ministry
fields.details:
Youth ministry, also commonly referred to as youth group, is an age-specific ministry at UCC Bwaise which carry out youth ministry to involve and engage with young people.

The moto of the youth ministry is WHATEVER YOUR HANDS FIND TO DO, DO IT WITH MIGHTY

Key Scripture:

Ecclesiastes 9:10

10 Whatever your hand finds to do, do it with all your might, for in the realm of the dead, where you are going, there is neither working nor planning nor knowledge nor wisdom.(NIV)

 

The main focus of this ministry are:

  • Prepare the future church ministers through giving the youth platform to minister.
  • To engage the youth and enable them find God's calling on their lives so that they might do God's will.
  • Encouraging young people (whether born again or not) to learn more about a given faith and to become more involved in spiritual life.
  • Providing open activities for the common good of the young people but with the main goal of Glorify Christ in Youthful stage of life.

The youth always gather on thursday from 5pm to 7pm to make practice for their service on Sunday starting at 4:00pm upto 7:00pm

fields.name: Virtuous Women Ministry
fields.details:
"Nga nesiimye nze okuba omukyala" literally translated as " am proud to be a woman"

At UCC Bwaise every female church member from 18 years and above is part of the women's ministry

They minister with vigor and their ministry helps to uplift the weak hearted and those who have lost hope in life.

The ministry always teaches womean to be proud of who they are and take pivotal role in the ministry at UCC Bwaise.

Things they do in their ministry include the following;

  1. Fellowshiping or making practices every thursday at 5pm
  2. Ministering through their recorded songs at church and outside the church.
  3. Engaging in different developmental church activities 
  4. Supporting each other in time of need.
  5. They have their own sacco which supports them financially

fields.about:
United Christian Centre Bwaise (UCC BWAISE) is a born again Christian church in Kampala Uganda East Africa.
The church is located on Bwaise - Nabweru road.
 The lead pastor is Pr. Joshua Zake ministering with a team of other associate pastors namely; Pr. Sande Posiano Zakumumpa, Pr. Henry Musubize, Pr. Sanyu Rebecca, Pr. Mukisa Kintu
and other preachers of the word including the following
Mr. John Bosco Buyuki, Mr. Charles Bunjo, Mr. Kasirye Eddie and others.

The following are ministries at UCC-Bwaise
Worship team
Children's ministry
Youth ministry
Women's ministry
Men's ministry
Teen's ministry
Evangelism ministry
Ushers ministry

Vision:  Discovering and Doing God's will
This is accomplished with the help of a Church Mission Lwaki oli mulamu (why are you alive) Teach Me To do your will, for you are my God(Psalms 143:10).(John 18:37)

Mission: " Lwaki Oli Mulamu(Why are you alive)"
This mission is accomplished by broadcasting on Christian radio with a program running on Innerman fm every Sunday morning at 6:30 - 7:30 am Uganda time .this frequency is also accessible online by app  InnerMan2 fm

The church also has an outreach ministry of Lwaki oli mulamu (why are you alive) missions with seminars almost every month both within and outside the country.

Pastor Joshua Zake has written several audio and video messages and Christian books for spiritual nourishments such as;
1. The inner burning
2. An upright heart
3. What can a Christian do amidst the storm
4. Why are you Alive

fields.mission_description:
WHY ARE YOU ALIVE
Introduction 
This is a very fundamental question in our lives. It deals with the reason why someone is in existence. It is important for each one of us to discover why they are alive. So many people have failed to discover the purpose of their lives and many have actually come to the end of their ΓÇÿjourneysΓÇÖ without getting the slightest idea of why they ever lived.
The scriptures teach us that the of spirit ΓÇ£mankindΓÇ¥ existed long before the creation of the world.
The creation of mankind happened in the eternity before God created any other thing in the physical world.
Wisdom  who is Christ , in Proverbs tell the story of what happened before the physical world was created - Prov 8:22  
As Christ tell the story he tells us of his moments with mankind in Spiritual world before the physical world was created 
Verse 31 ΓÇ£Rejoicing in the habitable part of his earth; and my delights were with the sons of menΓÇ¥.

The Psalmist through the prayer of Moses also reveals that spirit of mankind lived with God long before coming to the earth. 

 ΓÇ£A Prayer of Moses the man of God. Lord, thou hast been our dwelling place in all generationsΓÇ¥. Psalms 90:1

And that spirit existed before the body and even the days of mankind were known to God even before he was manifested on earth. ΓÇ£Your eyes saw my unformed Body. All the days ordained for me were written in your book before one of them came to be. Psalm 139:16.
This actually explains why manΓÇÖs spirit has got to return ΓÇ£to God, who gave it.ΓÇ¥ Ecclesiastes 12:7.

God predestined a lot of things about mankind. He knows each person and He selected them for His purpose. According to the Bible, even before one is born, they are known to God.
  ΓÇ£I knew you before I formed you in your motherΓÇÖs womb.ΓÇ¥ Jeremiah 1: 5
29ΓÇ¥For God knew his people in advance, and he chose them to become like his Son, so that his son would be the firstborn, with many brothers and sister. 30 And having chosen them, he called them to come to him. And he gave them right standing with himself, and he promised them his glory.ΓÇ¥ Romans 8:29-30

ItΓÇÖs God who chose when the spirit mankind should come on planet earth and definitely when it shall return to Him.  God determines birthdays and death days as the Bible states that ΓÇÿThe length of manΓÇÖs life is decided beforehand.ΓÇÖ Job 14:5

The best way you can get to know why you are alive is by getting to know your origin. The Bible states in Genesis 1:26 that ΓÇ£Then God said, ΓÇ£And now we will make human beings; they will be like us and resemble us. They will have power over the fish, the birds and all animals, domestic and wild, large and small. So God created human beings, making them to be like to him. He created them male and female. In his own image in the image of God created He him male and female.ΓÇ¥
Being in the image of God means that man is a spiritual being dwelling in the physical world walking a physical journey. Otherwise,   the citizenship of mankind is in heaven as stated by Paul in Philippians 3:20.  However, God determines sets the times for every mankind and the exact places where they should live. He brings one forth at a point in time to move them in His own direction. Man is GodΓÇÖs messenger, a person sent from Heaven with a peculiar mission on earth.
 ΓÇ£Iam the one who spoke and called him; I led him out and gave him success. Now come close to me and hear what I say. From the beginning I have spoken openly and have always made my words come true. The Holy God of Israel, the Lord who saves, says Iam the Lord your God, the one who wants to teach you for your own good and direct you in the way you should go.ΓÇ¥ Isaiah 48:15-17 

The Bible sometimes refers to human beings as ΓÇÿChristΓÇÖs AmbassadorsΓÇÖ 1 Corinthians 5:20 to show that man is a representative of the heavenly kingdom here on earth. As an ambassador, man is on a heavenly mission on earth. He is an instrument of transformation that is supposed to bring about change in places or systems wherever they go. Man is specifically designed and set apart for a particular purpose (Jeremiah 1:5) which purpose is ordained by God to be a fulfilment in lives of other people; families, nations and generally the entire creation. Man is a part of GodΓÇÖs original project and according to (Psalms 139:16) God scheduled every day of your life before you came to be.

WHO ASKS WHY YOU ARE ALIVE?

The question ΓÇ£Why one is aliveΓÇ¥ can be asked by God, by fellow men or the individual Christian. 
It is a very fundamental question which each one of should take time to meditate upon or else we abuse our stay on earth. T

his booklet is meant to help you to discover the reasons why you were created and why you are still on the face of the world. It will help you to know the reason and purpose for your being alive and how to set goals and ways of achieving a fulfilled life.

When you are able to fully understand why you are alive, you will be able to make a difference during your time. This will enhance the quality of your life and set you on the road to success and fulfilment.
But this will take the spirit of the Lord; you will need to humble yourself before God to be able to know His will for your life. Whatever it is, the reason for your ΓÇÿbeingΓÇÖ has a lot to do with your ΓÇÿcreatorΓÇÖ. 
The only possible reason why you appeared in a particular city, town or even family was for you to be released to your own generation to serve mankind and bring all things in your sphere of influence under the ruler ship of Christ. As it is stated in 1Corinthians 10:31 

1.	BY GOD
Through the word of God we come to learn about manΓÇÖs pre existence before coming into this world and therefore, there must be a reason why God decided to bring man on earth. There must have been a Godly plan which is called ΓÇÿGodΓÇÖs willΓÇÖ. 
Generations after generations, God has been sending ΓÇÿlivesΓÇÖ on the planet earth for a specific period of time.  During the given number of days, months or years that one lives, God keeps checking on manΓÇÖs progress but sometimes He wonders why some people, are still alive since they donΓÇÖt seem to be doing what He sent them to do. This is very unfortunate and the Bible says that ΓÇ£The axe is already at the root of the trees, and every tree that does not produce good fruit will be cut down and thrown in fire.ΓÇ¥ Mathew 3:10

Man is not an accident but a person appointed to be GodΓÇÖs servant even before he existed. According to Jeremiah 1:5, man has been set apart and appointed as GodΓÇÖs spokesperson. This means that each person has got what it takes to do GodΓÇÖs will. Whatever gifts God gives someone, He gives them so that one in turn gives them away in service to God. Everyone was created to share their life and talents with the community around them. When we become believers we also become GodΓÇÖs messengers. He wants to speak to the world through us and whatever we have gone through should be a message that God wants us to teach to others.

fields.news:
Now that we are in the end times, God is perfecting and fulfilling his own according to His will. 

Therefore, everyone must be ready for what is coming next on the list or agenda of God as far as His will is for us. 

Whenever God helps you attain a certain level or achievement, cerebrate it but focus ahead and quickly prepare for what is coming next because it is on its way coming! One of the reasons God communicates in his various ways of communication, is to PREPARE US! 

Even God in his capacity prepares before doing some things! 

Job 11:13 - If thou prepare thine heart, and stretch out thine hands toward him.

 Dan.10:12 - Then said he unto me, Fear not, Daniel: for from the first day that thou didst set thine heart to understand, and to chasten thyself before thy God, thy words were heard, and I am come for thy words.

 Prov. 24:27 - Prepare thy work without, and make it fit for thyself in the field; and afterwards build thine house. 

Prov. 30:25 - The ants are a people not strong, yet they prepare their meat in the summer; 

Isaiah 40:3 The voice of him that crieth in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the LORD, make straight in the desert a highway for our God. 

Isaiah 62:10 Go through, go through the gates; prepare ye the way of the people; cast up, cast up the highway; gather out the stones; lift up a standard for the people. 

Amos 4:12 - Therefore thus will I do unto thee, O Israel: and because I will do this unto thee, prepare to meet thy God, O Israel. 

Malachi 3:1 Behold, I will send my messenger, and he shall prepare the way before me: and the Lord, whom ye seek, shall suddenly come to his temple, even the messenger of the covenant, whom ye delight in: behold, he shall come, saith the LORD of hosts. 

– John the Baptist – Luke.1:76 John 14:3 - And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and receive you unto myself; that where I am, there ye may be also. 

Ish.38: 1 - In those days was Hezekiah sick unto death. And Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz came unto him, and said unto him, Thus saith the LORD, Set thine house in order: for thou shalt die, and not live. 

Titus 1:5 For this cause left I thee in Crete, that thou shouldest set in order the things that are wanting, and ordain elders in every city, as I had appointed thee:

 KEY THINGS WHEN GETTING PREPARED  

 1. What are you preparing for 

2. What state have you been in 

3. What are the ‘must does’ 

4. How much time do you have 

5. Learning and unlearning

fields.news:
God has a perfect and an original story of our lives.

The world has re-written most of our stories. BUT God has a perfect and an original story of our lives.

A re-written story is hard to live. God has a detailed information written about each one of us just as Jesus stated

“ as it was written about me”

– your story but as we go through this life, the world also tries to re- write your story editing and altering many things to make you believe that’s is how your destined.

God still has the original version of your story even though the devil has tried to lie and convince you through different happenings that the edited story is all you can be!

The way God designed life is that it begins small and then grows up to the very end which is helpful in many ways that experiences good or bad are divided up into blocks that the excitement and pressure are bearable.

Zech.4:10 - For who hath despised the day of small things? for they shall rejoice, and shall see the plummet in the hand of Zerubbabel with those seven; they are the eyes of the LORD, which run to and fro through the whole earth

Now that there are different stages of life, there are several experiences some common to all mankind, others unique to each individual yet others same but met at different stages and levels.

The journey of Life has got several junctions where decisions have to be made which decisions are so crucial that they will determine the next level of this journey or even the rest of the journey! Life has different stages, and there are activities that we have to do at each stage.

God has placed opportunities at each stage of life One of the greatest enemies of our destiny is man himself; Many times one ends up fighting against himself - what you are meant to be against what you choose to be!

Philip. 4:12 I know both how to be abased, and I know how to abound: everywhere and in all things I am instructed both to be full and to be hungry, both to abound and to suffer need.

Rev.7:14 – ( 9 – 14) And I said unto him, Sir, thou knowest. And he said to me, these are they which came out of great tribulation, and have washed their robes, and made them white in the blood of the Lamb.

2Pet.2:9 - The Lord knoweth how to deliver the godly out of temptations, and to reserve the unjust unto the day of judgment to be punished.

The story of life has the following attributes

  1. Questions
  2. Discouragements
  3. Competitors
  4. Advisers
  5. News Anchors
  6. Influencers
  7. Commentators 
  8. Spectators

Advisers good and bad This life if full of advisers both Good and bad, we therefore must very careful on the advises we take.

News anchors There people who specialize in taking news about you or bringing news about other people. Some of the news spread around is story destroyer or damaging.

Jer.20:15 - Cursed be the man who brought tidings to my father, saying a man child is born unto thee; making him very glad.

1Sam.31:4 - Then said Saul unto his armorbearer, Draw thy sword, and thrust me through therewith; lest these uncircumcised come and thrust me through, and abuse me. But his armorbearer would not; for he was sore afraid. Therefore Saul took a sword, and fell upon it. 5 And when his armorbearer saw that Saul was dead, he fell likewise upon his sword, and died with him.

Influencers and blockers Influencers Cause you to do what you would not have done or connect you but in the negative way! 

Commentators There some people that have a comment on anything and everything, they never reserve themselves They end becoming fault finders, fun makers, loose talkers or course jockers

Mat.12:36 – 37 - But I say unto you, that every idle word that men shall speak, they shall give account thereof in the day of judgment .37 for by thy words thou shalt be justified, and by thy words thou shalt be condemned.

Jude.1:16 - These are murmurers, complainers, walking after their own lusts; and their mouth speaketh great swelling words, having men's persons in admiration because of advantage.

Eph.5:4 - Neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not convenient: but rather giving of thanks.

Spectators Never participate but are on lookers/ watchers Scars – they are a sign of a story Time wasters: heavily loaded, asking for your time; escout me

Ps.37:23-24 - 23 The steps of a good man are ordered by the LORD: and he delighteth in his way.24 Though he fall, he shall not be utterly cast down: for the LORD upholdeth him with his hand

Psalms 145:14 The LORD upholdeth all that fall, and raiseth up all those that be bowed down.

Micah.7: 8 Rejoice not against me, O mine enemy: when I fall, I shall arise; when I sit in darkness, the LORD shall be a light unto you.

Mat.24:12 – 13 – he who stands to the end will be saved.

Heb.3:14 – we share in Christ if we hold firmly until the end. Just as the land scape has got such a terrain that is not even but with ups and downs formations, even life in many ways is uneven.

On this journey short or long, we encounter different people and opportunities; some of whom are good yet others are bad (positive and negative).

The Examples of People's Stories of life

1. JOSEPH

Joseph learnt lessons in his life story.

  • - He learnt that there are dream blockers in life
  • -He learnt that never trust mankind, they forget easily.
  • - There is no pit deep enough that God can not get you out and place you were he wants you to be.

Challenges that Joseph faced in his story of life

  • -He faced challenges that he never purposed for himself
  • -Pharoah's wife tried to seduce Joseph
  • -He was falsely accused by Pharoah's wife.
  • - He was mistreated by his brothers.

Joseph Faced Questions

  • -Did these dreams come from God or somewhere else?

Joseph faced Discouragements

  • -The cupbearer he interpreted a dream in prison forgot about him
  • -His brothers sold him Joseph faced Competition
  • -His brothers competed for favor from their father with Joseph

Joseph faced News Anchors in his Story of life.

  • -His brothers gave his father false news about Joseph for 10 years.

2 . A Life Story of Abraham

-He had to make decisions

- He had to learn lessons

Abraham is the first Hebrew. He is regarded highly by 3 major religions in their history;- Christians- Special relationship between the Jewish people( their Patriarch) and God- leading to believe that Jews are chosen by God Judaism – founding father of covenants

Abraham had a relationship with God for 100 years (Gen .12:4 to Gen.25:7) God was happy to call him his friend only him God calls his friends

Ish 41:8 - But thou, Israel, art my servant, Jacob whom I have chosen, the seed of Abraham my friend.

The transitional journey story of Abraham of 100 with God was a great journey Lessons This altar was built between She?em (shoulder, support) and Moreh (teacher). During the first stages of our walk with Elohim, we need a teacher (moreh) or teachers (morim) to guide us, to help us, to clarify things along the way, to teach and enlighten us.

fields.news:
There are Six foundations of Salvation

1. Foundation of Repentance

2. Foundation of faith towards God  

3. Foundation of baptism

4. Foundation of laying on of hands

5. Foundation of resurrection of the dead

6. Foundation of eternal judgement

 

Foundation of baptism

Kinds of baptism

a). Baptism of water for repentance

b). Baptism of  the Holy spirit

c). Baptism of suffering

 

Baptism of suffering

 

1Peter 5:10 This is meant to make a believer mature and become steadfast spiritually

Psalms 7:12 This suffering is not meant to harm us rather to transform, a journey of change in life of a believe.

luke 3:17 It is a time when God is winnowing wheat from rubbish, the testing to check if you know what you believed.

He uses these situations to shake believers to see who standing and those that are not.

Deu 8:3 Through suffering God humbles people so that they walk a journey of salvation well guided, it is a process of prunning, he chops off old branches and we get new branches. It is through enduring suffering to the end that a person can benefit from it but not in the middle of suffering.

 

The example of Joseph and Job, these men went through tough times of suffering but this was just a test of time.

The children of Israel while in the desert, they suffered hunger and thirst so that he would get only those who are steadfast to enter the promised land, this means God baptises people with fire

 

Mark 10:35-40 Jesus confirms that everyone who believes in him will be baptised with this suffering

Romans  5:3 It is a patient test for everyone

Isaiah 43:1-2 Amidst all this suffering, God is with us and he can not leave us alone but he will alwys stand with us to help us go through such suffering.

Suffering helps to bring back people to God, when people are pressed hard with suffering they tend to draw close to God.

Psalms 66:10-13 Through suffering God removes  

God takes us to wilderness to teaches us his ways and to conscrete us for the purpose of his Kingdom like he did to John the baptist. But if you are not so keen you might take long in the wilderness.

 

Conclusively:

Prepare your heart so that when God is taking us through the wilderness we don't jump off but we stand still untill we have been fully prunned

The storms are the challenges against our journey of life on earth

The storm is always for a moment in your life But if you never knew about the storm, you might curse God but the storm is a minister of God

The storm maybe loud but the voice of the Lord amidst the storm is always louder

A storm does not mean that God is not with you, but when you hearken to his voice you will hear a voice of victory ahead of the storm.

Kinds of Storms

1. An abrupt storm

2. A storm amidst the storm

3 A mild Storm

fields.title: Preparing for what is next
fields.details:
Now that we are in the end times, God is perfecting and fulfilling his own according to His will.

Therefore, everyone must be ready for what is coming next on the list or agenda of God as far as His will is for us.

 

Whenever God helps you attain a certain level or achievement, cerebrate 
it but focus ahead and quickly prepare for what is coming next because it is on its way coming!

 

One of the reasons God communicates in his various ways of communication, is to PREPARE US!

Even God in his capacity prepares before doing some things!

 

Scriptures to help us get more context on this matter.

  1. Job 11:13 - If thou prepare thine heart, and stretch out thine hands toward him.
  2. Dan.10:12 - Then said he unto me, Fear not, Daniel: for from the first day that thou didst set thine heart to understand, and to chasten thyself before thy God, thy words were heard, and I am come for thy words.
  3. Prov. 24:27 - Prepare thy work without, and make it fit for thyself in the field; and afterwards build thine house.
  4. Prov. 30:25 - The ants are a people not strong, yet they prepare their meat in the summer;
  5. Isaiah 40:3 The voice of him that crieth in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the LORD, make straight in the desert a highway for our God.
  6. Isaiah 62:10 Go through, go through the gates; prepare ye the way of the people; cast up, cast up the highway; gather out the stones; lift up a standard for the people.
  7. Amos 4:12 - Therefore thus will I do unto thee, O Israel: and because I will do this unto thee, prepare to meet thy God, O Israel.
  8. Malachi 3:1 Behold, I will send my messenger, and he shall prepare the way before me: and the Lord, whom ye seek, shall suddenly come to his temple, even the messenger of the covenant, whom ye delight in: behold, he shall come, saith the LORD of hosts. – John the Baptist – Luke.1:76
  9. John 14:3 - And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and receive you unto myself; that where I am, there ye may be also.
  10. Ish.38: 1 - In those days was Hezekiah sick unto death. And Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz came unto him, and said unto him, Thus saith the LORD, Set thine house in order: for thou shalt die, and not live.
  11. Titus 1:5 For this cause left I thee in Crete, that thou shouldest set in order the things that are wanting, and ordain elders in every city, as I had appointed thee:

KEY THINGS WHEN GETTING PREPARED
 
1. What are you preparing for
2. What state have you been in
3. What are the ‘must does’
4. How much time do you have
5. Learning and unlearning
